  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Using renewable energy to improve livelihoods for Kenya&apos;&apos;s fisherfolk</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenyans living on the shore of Lake Victoria are amongst the poorest in East Africa. Over two-thirds of them live below the poverty line and rely heavily on fishing for food and money. Without electricity for chilling or freezing, fish are highly perishable and must be sold or consumed soon after landing, leaving local fishermen with no bargaining power to get a fair price for their catch. This project will provide appropriate technology, such as affordable small-scale solutions for renewable energy from wind and solar sources, and equipment to keep fish cold. It will also provide training to fishermen, traders and farmers. It will support people to find other jobs thereby diversifying their diet and reducing risks, and encourage entrepreneurs to switch to &#x2018;greener&#x2019; products. As a result people will increase their income and improve their nutrition and health.</narrative>
  </description>
